11/04/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- European Parliament President Josep Borrell hailed Macedonia's progress Monday (10 April) in the reform process and EU integration, saying the country deserves EU candidate status. Borrell, on a daylong visit to Skopje, was addressing the Macedonian legislature. He also praised the level of multiethnic co-existence achieved since the end of the 2001 interethnic conflict.
In other news, the new National Co-ordination Centre for Border Management officially opened in Skopje on Monday. The project -- the first of its kind in the Western Balkans -- was financed by the European Agency for Reconstruction. (Makfax, Telma TV, A1 TV - 10/04/06)
